						               													<description>Shuffle Game of Life Card Game&amp;#10;The aim of the game is to get 100 life points, the first player to play all of their cards onto the table wins. To play cards on the table players must build sets and runs of cards, rummy style.&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Shuffle Game of Life is an exciting card game version of the popular board game, perfect for travelling and a quicker game! The game play lasts for approximately 20 minutes and is suitable for ages 7+ with 2-4 players&amp;#10;The aim of the game is to be the first person to get 100 life points by getting rid of all the cards in your hand by playing them onto the table. To play cards onto the table you must be able to make sets and runs or add to other players sets and runs. How to play &amp;ndash; Each card is worth a certain number of points which accumulate as you play them onto the table. At the start of your turn take a card from the draw pile or discard pile (your choice), if you can make a set or runs then play them onto the table in front of you.&amp;#10;A set is three or four cards showing the same career or house but in different colours. A run is three or more consecutively numbered cards of the same colour. If you can add cards to another players set or run on the table during your turn. &amp;#10;You need to play all the cards from you hand as quickly as possible to score life points, that&amp;rsquo;s why it is worth adding to other players sets and runs. The game also includes wild spinner cards these can be any number to complete a set. At the end of your turn you must always discard a card onto the discard pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
